1.Check Flutter installation

Run flutter --version in the terminal  :-  Flutter displays the installed Flutter SDK version, Dart version, and 
                                           channel (e.g., Stable), confirming that Flutter is installed and added to the system PATH.

2. Check environment configuration

Run flutter doctor  :-  Flutter displays a report with green check marks (✓) for Flutter, Android toolchain, Android Studio, connected 
                        devices, and other required components. Any missing components or issues are shown with warnings or errors.

3. Verify connected devices

Run flutter devices  :-  Flutter lists all connected physical devices, emulators, or desktop devices available for running Flutter 
                         applications. If a device is detected, it will appear with its name and platform.
